12-16 West 86th Street, south side, west of Central Park West.
About 1913.
title: Manhattan: 86th Street (West) - Central Park West

text:
Central Park: A view of W.P.A. employees removing the 86th Street car tracks in the western side of the Park on a transverse vehicular road that extends from West 86th Street and Central Park West to East 85th Street and Fifth Ave. This photo is taken slightly eastward of the first point.

September 29, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
title: Manhattan: Central Park - Transverse roads.

text:
Central Park: W.P.A. employees removing the 86th Street, crosstown car tracks that were laid on a transverse vehicular road through the Park. They ran in an easterly and westerly direction from West 86th Street and Central Park West to East 85th Street and Fifth Ave. This view is slightly eastward of the first point.

September 29, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
title: Manhattan: Central Park - Transverse roads.
